56static inline String computeKeyURL(const URL& url)
57{
58 URL keyURL { url };
59 keyURL.removeQueryAndFragmentIdentifier();
60 return keyURL.string();
61}
62
63static inline Vector<uint64_t> queryCache(const Vector<RecordInformation>* records, const ResourceRequest& request, const CacheQueryOptions& options)
64{
65 if (!records)
66 return { };
67
68 if (!options.ignoreMethod && request.httpMethod() != "GET")
69 return { };
70
71 Vector<uint64_t> results;
72 for (const auto& record : *records) {
73 if (WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::queryCacheMatch(request, record.url, record.hasVaryStar, record.varyHeaders, options))
74 results.append(record.identifier);
75 }
76 return results;
77}
78
79static inline void updateVaryInformation(RecordInformation& recordInformation, const ResourceRequest& request, const ResourceResponse& response)
80{
81 auto varyValue = response.httpHeaderField(WebCore::HTTPHeaderName::Vary);
82 if (varyValue.isNull()) {
83 recordInformation.hasVaryStar = false;
84 recordInformation.varyHeaders = { };
85 return;
86 }
87
88 varyValue.split(',', [&](StringView view) {
89 if (!recordInformation.hasVaryStar && stripLeadingAndTrailingHTTPSpaces(view) == "*")
90 recordInformation.hasVaryStar = true;
91 String headerName = view.toString();
92 recordInformation.varyHeaders.add(headerName, request.httpHeaderField(headerName));
93 });
94
95 if (recordInformation.hasVaryStar)
96 recordInformation.varyHeaders = { };
97}
98
99RecordInformation Cache::toRecordInformation(const Record& record)
100{
101 Key key { "record"_s, m_uniqueName, { }, createCanonicalUUIDString(), m_caches.salt() };
102 RecordInformation recordInformation { WTFMove(key), MonotonicTime::now().secondsSinceEpoch().milliseconds(), record.identifier, 0 , record.responseBodySize, record.request.url(), false, { } };
103
104 updateVaryInformation(recordInformation, record.request, record.response);
105
106 return recordInformation;
107}

130static RecordInformation isolatedCopy(const RecordInformation& information)
131{
132 auto result = RecordInformation { information.key, information.insertionTime, information.identifier, information.updateResponseCounter, information.size, information.url.isolatedCopy(), information.hasVaryStar, { } };
133 HashMap<String, String> varyHeaders;
134 for (const auto& keyValue : information.varyHeaders)
135 varyHeaders.set(keyValue.key.isolatedCopy(), keyValue.value.isolatedCopy());
136 result.varyHeaders = WTFMove(varyHeaders);
137 return result;
138}
139
140struct TraversalResult {
141 uint64_t cacheIdentifier;
142 HashMap<String, Vector<RecordInformation>> records;
143 Vector<Key> failedRecords;
144};
145
146static TraversalResult isolatedCopy(TraversalResult&& result)
147{
148 HashMap<String, Vector<RecordInformation>> isolatedRecords;
149 for (auto& keyValue : result.records) {
150 auto& recordVector = keyValue.value;
151 for (size_t cptr = 0; cptr < recordVector.size(); cptr++)
152 recordVector[cptr] = isolatedCopy(recordVector[cptr]);
153
154 isolatedRecords.set(keyValue.key.isolatedCopy(), WTFMove(recordVector));
155 }
156
157 // No need to isolate keys since they are isolated through the copy constructor
158 return TraversalResult { result.cacheIdentifier, WTFMove(isolatedRecords), WTFMove(result.failedRecords) };
159}

161void Cache::open(CompletionCallback&& callback)
162{
163 if (m_state == State::Open) {
164 callback(std::nullopt);
165 return;
166 }
167 if (m_state == State::Opening) {
168 m_pendingOpeningCallbacks.append(WTFMove(callback));
169 return;
170 }
171 m_state = State::Opening;
172 TraversalResult traversalResult { m_identifier, { }, { } };
173 m_caches.readRecordsList(*this, [caches = makeRef(m_caches), callback = WTFMove(callback), traversalResult = WTFMove(traversalResult)](const auto* storageRecord, const auto&) mutable {
174 if (!storageRecord) {
175 RunLoop::main().dispatch([caches = WTFMove(caches), callback = WTFMove(callback), traversalResult = isolatedCopy(WTFMove(traversalResult)) ]() mutable {
176 for (auto& key : traversalResult.failedRecords)
177 caches->removeCacheEntry(key);
178
179 auto* cache = caches->find(traversalResult.cacheIdentifier);
180 if (!cache) {
181 callback(Error::Internal);
182 return;
183 }
184 cache->m_records = WTFMove(traversalResult.records);
185 cache->finishOpening(WTFMove(callback), std::nullopt);
186 });
187 return;
188 }
189
190 auto decoded = decodeRecordHeader(*storageRecord);
191 if (!decoded) {
192 traversalResult.failedRecords.append(storageRecord->key);
193 return;
194 }
195
196 auto& record = decoded->record;
197 auto insertionTime = decoded->insertionTime;
198
199 RecordInformation recordInformation { storageRecord->key, insertionTime, 0, 0, record.responseBodySize, record.request.url(), false, { } };
200 updateVaryInformation(recordInformation, record.request, record.response);
201
202 auto& sameURLRecords = traversalResult.records.ensure(computeKeyURL(recordInformation.url), [] { return Vector<RecordInformation> { }; }).iterator->value;
203 sameURLRecords.append(WTFMove(recordInformation));
204 });
205}
206
207void Cache::finishOpening(CompletionCallback&& callback, std::optional<Error>&& error)
208{
209 Vector<std::reference_wrapper<RecordInformation>> records;
210 for (auto& value : m_records.values()) {
211 for (auto& record : value)
212 records.append(record);
213 }
214 std::sort(records.begin(), records.end(), [&](const auto& a, const auto& b) {
215 return a.get().insertionTime < b.get().insertionTime;
216 });
217 for (auto& record : records)
218 record.get().identifier = ++m_nextRecordIdentifier;
219
220 if (error) {
221 m_state = State::Uninitialized;
222 callback(error.value());
223 auto callbacks = WTFMove(m_pendingOpeningCallbacks);
224 for (auto& callback : callbacks)
225 callback(error.value());
226 return;
227 }
228 m_state = State::Open;
229
230 callback(std::nullopt);
231 auto callbacks = WTFMove(m_pendingOpeningCallbacks);
232 for (auto& callback : callbacks)
233 callback(std::nullopt);
234}

236class ReadRecordTaskCounter : public RefCounted<ReadRecordTaskCounter> {
237public:
238 using ReadRecordsCallback = WTF::Function<void(Vector<Record>&&, Vector<uint64_t>&&)>;
239 static Ref<ReadRecordTaskCounter> create(ReadRecordsCallback&& callback) { return adoptRef(*new ReadRecordTaskCounter(WTFMove(callback))); }
240
241 ~ReadRecordTaskCounter()
242 {
243 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
244 if (!m_callback)
245 return;
246 std::sort(m_records.begin(), m_records.end(), [&] (const auto& a, const auto& b) {
247 return a.identifier < b.identifier;
248 });
249 m_callback(WTFMove(m_records), WTFMove(m_failedRecords));
250 }
251
252 void appendRecord(Expected<Record, Error>&& result, uint64_t recordIdentifier, uint64_t updateCounter)
253 {
254 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
255 if (!result.has_value()) {
256 m_failedRecords.append(recordIdentifier);
257 return;
258 }
259 result.value().identifier = recordIdentifier;
260 result.value().updateResponseCounter = updateCounter;
261 m_records.append(WTFMove(result.value()));
262 }
263
264private:
265 explicit ReadRecordTaskCounter(ReadRecordsCallback&& callback)
266 : m_callback(WTFMove(callback))
267 {
268 }
269
270 ReadRecordsCallback m_callback;
271 Vector<Record> m_records;
272 Vector<uint64_t> m_failedRecords;
273};
274
275void Cache::retrieveRecord(const RecordInformation& record, Ref<ReadRecordTaskCounter>&& taskCounter)
276{
277 readRecordFromDisk(record, [caches = makeRef(m_caches), identifier = m_identifier, recordIdentifier = record.identifier, updateCounter = record.updateResponseCounter, taskCounter = WTFMove(taskCounter)](Expected<Record, Error>&& result) mutable {
278 auto* cache = caches->find(identifier);
279 if (!cache)
280 return;
281 taskCounter->appendRecord(WTFMove(result), recordIdentifier, updateCounter);
282 });
283}
284
285void Cache::retrieveRecords(const RetrieveRecordsOptions& options, RecordsCallback&& callback)
286{
287 ASSERT(m_state == State::Open);
288
289 auto taskCounter = ReadRecordTaskCounter::create([caches = makeRef(m_caches), identifier = m_identifier, shouldProvideResponse = options.shouldProvideResponse, callback = WTFMove(callback)](Vector<Record>&& records, Vector<uint64_t>&& failedRecordIdentifiers) mutable {
290 auto* cache = caches->find(identifier);
291 if (cache)
292 cache->removeFromRecordList(failedRecordIdentifiers);
293
294 if (!shouldProvideResponse) {
295 for (auto& record : records) {
296 record.response = { };
297 record.responseBody = nullptr;
298 record.responseBodySize = 0;
299 }
300 }
301 callback(WTFMove(records));
302 });
303
304 if (options.request.url().isNull()) {
305 for (auto& records : m_records.values()) {
306 for (auto& record : records)
307 retrieveRecord(record, taskCounter.copyRef());
308 }
309 return;
310 }
311
312 if (!options.ignoreMethod && options.request.httpMethod() != "GET")
313 return;
314
315 auto* records = recordsFromURL(options.request.url());
316 if (!records)
317 return;
318
319 CacheQueryOptions queryOptions { options.ignoreSearch, options.ignoreMethod, options.ignoreVary, { } };
320 for (auto& record : *records) {
321 if (DOMCacheEngine::queryCacheMatch(options.request, record.url, record.hasVaryStar, record.varyHeaders, queryOptions))
322 retrieveRecord(record, taskCounter.copyRef());
323 }
324}
325
326RecordInformation& Cache::addRecord(Vector<RecordInformation>* records, const Record& record)
327{
328 if (!records) {
329 auto key = computeKeyURL(record.request.url());
330 ASSERT(!m_records.contains(key));
331 records = &m_records.set(key, Vector<RecordInformation> { }).iterator->value;
332 }
333 records->append(toRecordInformation(record));
334 return records->last();
335}
336
337Vector<RecordInformation>* Cache::recordsFromURL(const URL& url)
338{
339 auto iterator = m_records.find(computeKeyURL(url));
340 if (iterator == m_records.end())
341 return nullptr;
342 return &iterator->value;
343}
344
345const Vector<RecordInformation>* Cache::recordsFromURL(const URL& url) const
346{
347 auto iterator = m_records.find(computeKeyURL(url));
348 if (iterator == m_records.end())
349 return nullptr;
350 return &iterator->value;
351}

353class AsynchronousPutTaskCounter : public RefCounted<AsynchronousPutTaskCounter> {
354public:
355 static Ref<AsynchronousPutTaskCounter> create(RecordIdentifiersCallback&& callback) { return adoptRef(*new AsynchronousPutTaskCounter(WTFMove(callback))); }
356 ~AsynchronousPutTaskCounter()
357 {
358 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
359 if (!m_callback)
360 return;
361 if (m_error) {
362 m_callback(makeUnexpected(m_error.value()));
363 return;
364 }
365 m_callback(WTFMove(m_recordIdentifiers));
366 }
367
368 void setError(Error error)
369 {
370 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
371 if (m_error)
372 return;
373
374 m_error = error;
375 }
376
377 void addRecordIdentifier(uint64_t identifier)
378 {
379 m_recordIdentifiers.append(identifier);
380 }
381
382private:
383 explicit AsynchronousPutTaskCounter(RecordIdentifiersCallback&& callback)
384 : m_callback(WTFMove(callback))
385 {
386 }
387
388 std::optional<Error> m_error;
389 RecordIdentifiersCallback m_callback;
390 Vector<uint64_t> m_recordIdentifiers;
391};
392
393void Cache::storeRecords(Vector<Record>&& records, RecordIdentifiersCallback&& callback)
394{
395 auto taskCounter = AsynchronousPutTaskCounter::create(WTFMove(callback));
396
397 WebCore::CacheQueryOptions options;
398 for (auto& record : records) {
399 auto* sameURLRecords = recordsFromURL(record.request.url());
400 auto matchingRecords = queryCache(sameURLRecords, record.request, options);
401
402 auto position = !matchingRecords.isEmpty() ? sameURLRecords->findMatching([&](const auto& item) { return item.identifier == matchingRecords[0]; }) : notFound;
403
404 if (position == notFound) {
405 record.identifier = ++m_nextRecordIdentifier;
406 taskCounter->addRecordIdentifier(record.identifier);
407
408 auto& recordToWrite = addRecord(sameURLRecords, record);
409 writeRecordToDisk(recordToWrite, WTFMove(record), taskCounter.copyRef(), 0);
410 } else {
411 auto& existingRecord = sameURLRecords->at(position);
412 taskCounter->addRecordIdentifier(existingRecord.identifier);
413 updateRecordToDisk(existingRecord, WTFMove(record), taskCounter.copyRef());
414 }
415 }
416}
417
418void Cache::put(Vector<Record>&& records, RecordIdentifiersCallback&& callback)
419{
420 ASSERT(m_state == State::Open);
421
422 WebCore::CacheQueryOptions options;
423 CheckedUint64 spaceRequired = 0;
424
425 for (auto& record : records) {
426 auto* sameURLRecords = recordsFromURL(record.request.url());
427 auto matchingRecords = queryCache(sameURLRecords, record.request, options);
428
429 auto position = (sameURLRecords && !matchingRecords.isEmpty()) ? sameURLRecords->findMatching([&](const auto& item) { return item.identifier == matchingRecords[0]; }) : notFound;
430
431 spaceRequired += record.responseBodySize;
432 if (position != notFound) {
433 uint64_t spaceDecreased = sameURLRecords->at(position).size;
434 if (spaceRequired >= spaceDecreased)
435 spaceRequired -= spaceDecreased;
436 }
437 }
438
439 if (spaceRequired.hasOverflowed()) {
440 callback(makeUnexpected(DOMCacheEngine::Error::QuotaExceeded));
441 return;
442 }
443
444 m_caches.requestSpace(spaceRequired, [caches = makeRef(m_caches), identifier = m_identifier, records = WTFMove(records), callback = WTFMove(callback)](std::optional<DOMCacheEngine::Error>&& error) mutable {
445 if (error) {
446 callback(makeUnexpected(error.value()));
447 return;
448 }
449 auto* cache = caches->find(identifier);
450 if (!cache) {
451 callback(makeUnexpected(DOMCacheEngine::Error::Internal));
452 return;
453 }
454 cache->storeRecords(WTFMove(records), WTFMove(callback));
455 });
456}

458void Cache::remove(WebCore::ResourceRequest&& request, WebCore::CacheQueryOptions&& options, RecordIdentifiersCallback&& callback)
459{
460 ASSERT(m_state == State::Open);
461
462 auto* records = recordsFromURL(request.url());
463 auto recordIdentifiers = queryCache(records, request, options);
464 if (recordIdentifiers.isEmpty()) {
465 callback({ });
466 return;
467 }
468
469 records->removeAllMatching([this, &recordIdentifiers](auto& item) {
470 bool shouldRemove = recordIdentifiers.findMatching([&item](auto identifier) { return identifier == item.identifier; }) != notFound;
471 if (shouldRemove)
472 this->removeRecordFromDisk(item);
473 return shouldRemove;
474 });
475
476 // This operation would change caches size, so make sure callback finishes after size file is updated.
477 m_caches.updateSizeFile([callback = WTFMove(callback), recordIdentifiers = WTFMove(recordIdentifiers)]() mutable {
478 callback(WTFMove(recordIdentifiers));
479 });
480}
481
482void Cache::removeFromRecordList(const Vector<uint64_t>& recordIdentifiers)
483{
484 if (recordIdentifiers.isEmpty())
485 return;
486
487 for (auto& records : m_records.values()) {
488 auto* cache = this;
489 records.removeAllMatching([cache, &recordIdentifiers](const auto& item) {
490 return notFound != recordIdentifiers.findMatching([cache, &item](const auto& identifier) {
491 if (item.identifier != identifier)
492 return false;
493 cache->removeRecordFromDisk(item);
494 return true;
495 });
496 });
497 }
498}

500void Cache::writeRecordToDisk(const RecordInformation& recordInformation, Record&& record, Ref<AsynchronousPutTaskCounter>&& taskCounter, uint64_t previousRecordSize)
501{
502 m_caches.writeRecord(*this, recordInformation, WTFMove(record), previousRecordSize, [taskCounter = WTFMove(taskCounter)](std::optional<Error>&& error) {
503 if (error)
504 taskCounter->setError(error.value());
505 });
506}
507
508void Cache::updateRecordToDisk(RecordInformation& existingRecord, Record&& record, Ref<AsynchronousPutTaskCounter>&& taskCounter)
509{
510 ++existingRecord.updateResponseCounter;
511 readRecordFromDisk(existingRecord, [caches = makeRef(m_caches), identifier = m_identifier, recordIdentifier = existingRecord.identifier, record = WTFMove(record), taskCounter = WTFMove(taskCounter)](Expected<Record, Error>&& result) mutable {
512 if (!result.has_value())
513 return;
514
515 auto* cache = caches->find(identifier);
516 if (!cache)
517 return;
518
519 auto* sameURLRecords = cache->recordsFromURL(result.value().request.url());
520 if (!sameURLRecords)
521 return;
522
523 auto position = sameURLRecords->findMatching([&] (const auto& item) { return item.identifier == recordIdentifier; });
524 if (position == notFound)
525 return;
526 auto& recordInfo = sameURLRecords->at(position);
527 auto previousSize = recordInfo.size;
528 recordInfo.size = record.responseBodySize;
529
530 auto& recordFromDisk = result.value();
531 record.requestHeadersGuard = recordFromDisk.requestHeadersGuard;
532 record.request = WTFMove(recordFromDisk.request);
533 record.options = WTFMove(recordFromDisk.options);
534 record.referrer = WTFMove(recordFromDisk.referrer);
535
536 updateVaryInformation(recordInfo, record.request, record.response);
537
538 cache->writeRecordToDisk(recordInfo, WTFMove(record), WTFMove(taskCounter), previousSize);
539 });
540}

552Storage::Record Cache::encode(const RecordInformation& recordInformation, const Record& record)
553{
554 WTF::Persistence::Encoder encoder;
555 encoder << recordInformation.insertionTime;
556 encoder << recordInformation.size;
557 encoder << record.requestHeadersGuard;
558 record.request.encodeWithoutPlatformData(encoder);
559 record.options.encodePersistent(encoder);
560 encoder << record.referrer;
561
562 encoder << record.responseHeadersGuard;
563 encoder << record.response;
564 encoder << record.responseBodySize;
565
566 encoder.encodeChecksum();
567
568 Data header(encoder.buffer(), encoder.bufferSize());
569 Data body;
570 WTF::switchOn(record.responseBody, [](const Ref<WebCore::FormData>& formData) {
571 // FIXME: Store form data body.
572 }, [&](const Ref<WebCore::SharedBuffer>& buffer) {
573 body = { buffer->data(), buffer->size() };
574 }, [](const std::nullptr_t&) {
575 });
576
577 return { recordInformation.key, { }, header, body, { } };
578}

580static std::optional<WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record> decodeDOMCacheRecord(WTF::Persistence::Decoder& decoder)
581{
582 std::optional<FetchHeaders::Guard> requestHeadersGuard;
583 decoder >> requestHeadersGuard;
584 if (!requestHeadersGuard)
585 return std::nullopt;
586
587 ResourceRequest request;
588 if (!request.decodeWithoutPlatformData(decoder))
589 return std::nullopt;
590
591 FetchOptions options;
592 if (!FetchOptions::decodePersistent(decoder, options))
593 return std::nullopt;
594
595 std::optional<String> referrer;
596 decoder >> referrer;
597 if (!referrer)
598 return std::nullopt;
599
600 std::optional<FetchHeaders::Guard> responseHeadersGuard;
601 decoder >> responseHeadersGuard;
602 if (!responseHeadersGuard)
603 return std::nullopt;
604
605 ResourceResponse response;
606 if (!ResourceResponse::decode(decoder, response))
607 return std::nullopt;
608
609 std::optional<uint64_t> responseBodySize;
610 decoder >> responseBodySize;
611 if (!responseBodySize)
612 return std::nullopt;
613
614 if (!decoder.verifyChecksum())
615 return std::nullopt;
616
617 return {{
618 0,
619 0,
620 WTFMove(*requestHeadersGuard),
621 WTFMove(request),
622 WTFMove(options),
623 WTFMove(*referrer),
624 WTFMove(*responseHeadersGuard),
625 WTFMove(response),
626 { },
627 WTFMove(*responseBodySize)
628 }};
629}
630
631std::optional<Cache::DecodedRecord> Cache::decodeRecordHeader(const Storage::Record& storage)
632{
633 WTF::Persistence::Decoder decoder(storage.header.data(), storage.header.size());
634
635 std::optional<double> insertionTime;
636 decoder >> insertionTime;
637 if (!insertionTime)
638 return std::nullopt;
639
640 std::optional<uint64_t> size;
641 decoder >> size;
642 if (!size)
643 return std::nullopt;
644
645 std::optional<WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::Record> record = decodeDOMCacheRecord(decoder);
646 if (!record)
647 return std::nullopt;
648
649 return {{
650 WTFMove(*insertionTime),
651 WTFMove(*size),
652 WTFMove(*record)
653 }};
654}
655
656std::optional<Record> Cache::decode(const Storage::Record& storage)
657{
658 auto result = decodeRecordHeader(storage);
659
660 if (!result)
661 return std::nullopt;
662
663 auto record = WTFMove(result->record);
664 record.responseBody = WebCore::SharedBuffer::create(storage.body.data(), storage.body.size());
665
666 return record;
667}
668
669Vector<Key> Cache::keys() const
670{
671 Vector<Key> keys;
672 for (auto& records : m_records.values()) {
673 for (auto& record : records)
674 keys.append(record.key);
675 }
676 return keys;
677}
